      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUDAH RED (8) had a favourable gate and was too good at this track two runs ago. Drew wide last start and was easily accounted for, beaten 4.5 metres into fourth here over 1780m. Certainly cannot be faulted after that last effort and is good enough to put himself back in the winners' stall. UCANCALLME AL (1) finished third last start, beaten 30 metres at Albion Park over 2138m. Draws the pegs and expected to run well. NOTIONS (10) won two starts ago then things went wrong last start when she broke and finished 14 metres away in eighth over 1780m at this venue. Hard to know where she gets from this slightly awkward draw but rates a live chance in a similar assignment. STRAIGHTNNARROW (6) must be included after winning his past two starts, the latest at this course a week ago. Hard to ignore winning form.",
